Package: dineExpand
Title: Dining-Specific Semantic Dictionary Expander
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Gopi Nath", "Vajpai",
    role  = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "gvajpai@udel.edu")
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Description: Expands seed dictionaries for dining and hospitality research
    using word embeddings pre-trained on 512,140 Yelp restaurant reviews.
    Provides restaurant-domain word vectors out of the box — no setup
    required beyond a one-time 33 MB download. Supports any theoretical
    construct relevant to dining research: revisit intention, food neophobia,
    authenticity, service quality, and more. Built on top of 'lexiExpand'
    for the core similarity engine, with dining-specific defaults and
    a dedicated vector training function for researchers who wish to train
    on their own restaurant corpus.
